I felt like i should update, seeing as how i haven't in a while. Also i needed to rant because i am royaly pissed off at my mom. 

  Our annual fair at lancaster is here and i want to go to this concert on wednesday, mom says i can go, but i can't drive myself. Although i'm PERFECTLY capable of driving myself! It frecking pisses me off!! i am 16 years old and i deserve to go an hour away to a concert. I don't want to be in a bubble anymore, (i'm currently in the i'm-the-youngest-so-mom-is-sheltering-me bubble, and i'm sick of it! I demand the freedom that is giving to someone who is previlaged to drive. If the DMV thinks i'm ok to drive, i don't see why my own mother won't! 

 That's really all i have at the momment, as i am too mad to think of anything else. I'll update again when i'm in a better mood. Thank you for your time. 



P.S DARRYL!!!  YOU NEED TO COME BACK!! I NEED A SHOULDER TO CRY ON! (WHEN KEALA IS IN THE BATHROOM)

i'm a sick puppy guys. I have the tonsilitus or however you spell it. I've been sick since sunday, but hopefully i'm better to go to camp. I really want to go. I might have to miss the concert with Nechelle too, which i'm really sad about. But i really don't know what else to say, so i'll talk to ya'll later. Wish for me to feel better

hi. keala told me to update, i have nothing better to do. 

I just came back from town, (lancaster) i didn't get much but it's ok. My brother is going to college on monday, and my mom is totally freaking out about it, i found it quite funny. (don't tell her i said that) 

Umm. i got nothing, i have no life, so i have nothing to post. So i'll get off now, later

WOO HOO!! NO PARENTS FOR 2 DAYS!!! TOGA!!! TOGA!!!

My parentals will be gone for two whole days! we totally need to have a party. Anyone who reads this, you more or less know where i live, throw me a party. Just get rid of kathy and we'll be good. So this is all that you guys need to get. 

Keala: food, explosives, and an emu

Darryl: the Booze, the chicks, the guys, and more booze

Steph: Whatever you think we need


Save me you guys. This will kill me if i stay with kat very long

Save me!!

jen.

I feel like i should update. I haven't in a while so i think I should. Well, my friend Aub is leaving tomorrow, i don't know when but hopefully it's after i give her her stuff. (BTW Aub i have your phone, it's at my house) and i few other things that i won't tell you about. 
 On saterday i went to the show with Keala, Aubry and Keith to see the Fantastic 4, it was a pretty cool movie. But before we went to the movie, Keith gave us all 60$ each! I was shocked, not even my parents would do that just for the hell of it. After the movie we went to Outback, it was alright, the food wasn't that great, the server wasn't very good at her job, and i didn't feel all that well during dinner. Yeah, it basically sucked. After dinner we went to Walmart and spent out remaining money. I ended up not getting much, but enough for me. 
  
Yesterday i went over to Keala's to help him with a project, but the project is strictly a need-to-know things to i won't discuss it. :)

And today...well i don't really know what i'm doing, i deffinatly need to shower, i feel icky. And don't anyone say anything! I shower almost every day, i didn't shower yesterday cause i didn't feel like it. But anyway i think i told you everything you need to know. I'll go now a wallow in my filth. See you all later

Jenn

GRRRR!!! The illness is making me go crazy!!! Boredom is a very serious illness that can make you go mad if you let it. I have the early signs; obsessive cleaning, moodyness, and the sudden urge to find work. It might not be too late to save me, but just in case it is i'll leave my most prized pocessions to my closest friends-

Aubry: I leave you my savings, spend it as i would like it to be spent.

Keala: I leave you my stuff, but only the ones you hold most dear to you, like Fred...and your shirt

To everyone else: Go nuts. I can't take most of these things with me where i'm going.

Yup, you guessed it...i'm going to Wisconsin, and not the good place either, it's the Western Part of Wisconsin, where they're Viking Fans. Wish me luck friends, remember me as a peacemaker, and a laugh. I shall miss you all terribly. The Goat will ride again!!!

NOTE; This is to inform everyone who reads that this patient can not be held responsible for her action as she is ill with the disease Boredomus Mostest Or plainly, Boredom. If any one comes by the house looking for the things that the patient has giving you then you will be escorted off the property. If you do not choose to cooperate we will have no choice but to shoot you down, or have a dozen 5 year old sicked on you. Which ever one you want.

Thank you for you time

ONE MORE DAY LEFT OF SCHOOL!!!! I'm soooooooo excited. 
  I would have updated tomorrow but i will be busy, and after school gets out i go to Wisconsin. I finally get to see my dad's family, it's been 3 years ago. 
  So i'm looking forward to doing absolutly nothing this summer. I'm hoping to get some employment, but it's not very likely it's going to happen. 

So it's bummed days for the next few months. But i have to go and make sure i have everything for Wisconsin. C-ya laters

DON'T MAKE ME FLY!!! PLEASE DON'T MAKE ME FLY!!! :*(

I am alive. for the most part. I'll be better after school is out.
  So yesterday i got my license, can you say exciting? I can. I'd love to stay and chat but i'm watching Charlie and the Chocolate Factory. 

So c-ya, later, adious, gazutite, farwell.

If any of you are wondering what the W word is, it's the most horrible word in the world; Weddings.

Yep. This is one of those moments that has it's ups and downs. 

On the upside; I don't have to worrying about many wedding plans because i'm just a bridesmaid. 
The downside; I'm in BOTH my sister's weddings, BOTH a bridesmaid, and i'm sure knowing my luck, i will have more to do with both weddings than i would like. 

I'm just glade i don't have to worry about this stuff for like another 5, 10, 20 years. Sry Keala, I'm taking my good old time tieing the knot.

Besides i'm trying to think about my dad, he has to deal with 2 weddings in the next 2 years, I don't want to overwhelm him with this kind of stuff, also i don't want to kill my mother with outrages wedding prices. 

Ok i'm out. c-ya

Well that's all the time i have I am Jen and this is 3rd period computer class signing off.

You take the Path of Least Resistance. 

Why make things hard for yourself? You are a go-with-flow sort of person and little gets to you. Why? Because it's all good, right? They say the path of least resistance is a straight line and that's where you go, ever forward and never looking back. It's good to keep the past behind you, a quality far too little people have these days. You know the past is the past, but don't let yourself forget it. You can't learn from your mistakes if you don't remember them. You're probably loved for your laid-back frame of mind and easy-going qualities , but you tend take the easy way out in life and verge on lazy. 

  Great character is found through great challenges. You most likely have the abilities in you to succeed and over-come what life throws at you. You just got get up and face that challenge. You tend to lose your head in bad situations because you aren't used to them. And by the time you've found the easiest way to master a problem, you could've already taken care of it.

 Bad things happen, difficult situations come up, that's life. What matters is that you rise to face those challenges and you can do it. Never lose your laid-back qualities as they will help you greatly. Just step onto that hard road every once in awhile and you'll discover that with each stretch it becomes easier and easier to over-come life's hurdles.
